This paper is about designing a deep learning-based dialogue system, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on generating sarcastic and humorous responses, which is a subfield of NLP known as computational humor. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper involves training a seq2seq model, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, since the paper evaluates the system's performance using human raters, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a possible sub-category.
